title: DRAGNET (1967) 1-3 [retr?tv]
description:
DRAGNET (1967)
Dragnet 1967-1970 was the second run of the Dragnet series. It began in January of 1967, and ran to September of 1970. The lead character, Sgt. Joe Friday, was played by Jack Webb, who also directed and produced the series. The show&#039;s focus is on two detectives, Sgt. Joe Friday, and Officer Bill Gannon, played by Harry Morgan. The two track down criminals all throughout the city of Los Angeles, California.

1. The LSD Story   1/12/1967 
Sergeant Joe Friday and his partner Bill Gannon encounter a freaked-out young LSD user. This is the famous "Blue Boy" episode.
  Guest star: Eve Brent (Mrs. Carver), Michael Burns (Benjie "Blue Boy" Carver), Olan Soule (Ray Murray), Art Balinger (Capt. Lou Richey)

2. The Big Explosion    1/19/1967 
A neo-Nazi psycho has planted a bomb somewhere in L.A. Friday and Gannon have to find it.
  Guest star: Don Dubbins (Donald Chapman) , Harlan Warde (Captain Henry Mack), Bobby Troup (Al Amory), Olan Soule (Ray Murray), John Nolan (Nelson Groves), Ralph Moody (Matt Kemper), Kent McCord (Officer Martin), Ralph Manza (Gene Ellis), Bert Holland (Car Salesman), Val Avery (Phil Masturian)

3. The Kidnapping   1/26/1967 
Friday and Gannon help an employee rescue her kidnapped boss.
 Guest star: Harry Bartell (Ray Righetti), Art Balinger (Capt. Hugh Brown) , Peggy Webber (Janet Ohrmund)
